Flexible Single Master Operations (FSMO)
Check or Identify Current Server (PDC Emulator, RID Master, Domain Infrastructure Master, Naming Master, Schema Master)
Open Command line form any server and run this command.
  #netdom query fsmo

Change Role to another server
Open Command line from DC Server and run following commad.
  #ntdsutil
  #role
  #connections
  #connect to server SERVER_NAME     [target server which select for role]
  #quit         [quit from connection]
  #Transfer PDC               [Make connected server the PDC]
  #Transfer RID master       [Make connected server the RID master]
  #Transfer infrastructure master       [Make connected server the infrastructure master]
  #Transfer naming master             [Make connected server the naming master]
  #Transfer schema master             [Make connected server the schema master]
  #quit [for exit]

========== By GUI =========
For change PDC Emulator, RID Master, Infrastructure master open Active Directory users and computers from any server console.
Step 1:  Change the Domain Controller. Right click on "Active Directory users and computer" 
          then click change Domain Controller and selcet target Server and click okay.
Step 2: Right click on Domain name then clik "Oparation Master". then change each Role.

For change Domaning naming master Open Active Directory Domains and Trusts from any server console
Step 1:  Change the Domain Controller. Right click on "Active Directory Domains and Trusts" 
          then click change Domain Controller and selcet target Server and click okay.
Step 2: Right click on "Active Directory Domains and Trusts" then clik "Oparation Master". then change Role.
  
For change Schema master 
Step 1: regsvr32 schmmgmt.dll [Run this from command line]
Step 2: Open MMC: Type mmc in the Run box (Windows Key + R), then click File > Add/Remove Snap-in.
Step 3: Add Snap-in: Select Active Directory Schema from the list, click Add, and then OK
Step 4: Connect to Target DC: Right-click Active Directory Schema in the console, 
        select Change Domain Controller, choose the new DC, and click OK.
Step 5: Transfer Role: Right-click Active Directory Schema again, select Operations Master, click Change, and confirm with OK. 

